# Common Commands

Invoke with: *"how do I build"*, *"run locally"*, *"deploy"*, *"docker"*, *"what commands"*, *"npm scripts"*

Reference for all development, build, and deployment commands.

---

## 1. Development

### Start Development
```bash
npm install              # Install dependencies
npm run dev              # Start dashboard server (port 8080, ts-node)
npm run dev:poll         # Run poller manually (ts-node)
```

### Environment Variables (required for dev)
```bash
export REPORTPORTAL_URL=https://reportportal-cnv.apps...
export REPORTPORTAL_TOKEN=your-token-here

# Optional
export SLACK_WEBHOOK_URL=https://hooks.slack.com/services/...
export JIRA_URL=https://issues.redhat.com
export JIRA_TOKEN=your-jira-token
export SMTP_HOST=smtp.example.com
```

### Prerequisites
- Node.js >= 20
- npm
- Docker/Podman (for container builds)
- `oc` or `kubectl` (for cluster deployment)

---

## 2. Building

```bash
npm run build            # Compile TypeScript → dist/
```

### Production Run
```bash
npm run build            # Compile first
npm run start            # Run dashboard (node dist/serve.js)
npm run poll             # Run poller (node dist/index.js)
```

---

## 3. Code Quality

```bash
npm run build            # TypeScript compiler check (strict mode)
```

### Before Commit
```bash
npm run build            # Ensure no type errors
```

---

## 4. Docker

```bash
# Build image
podman build -t quay.io/openshift-cnv/cnv-console-monitor:latest .

# Run locally
podman run -it --rm \
  -p 8080:8080 \
  -e REPORTPORTAL_URL=... \
  -e REPORTPORTAL_TOKEN=... \
  -v ./data:/data \
  quay.io/openshift-cnv/cnv-console-monitor:latest

# Push to registry
podman push quay.io/openshift-cnv/cnv-console-monitor:latest
```

---

## 5. Kubernetes Deployment

```bash
# Deploy all resources
kubectl apply -f k8s/ -n cnv-monitor

# Individual resources
kubectl apply -f k8s/configmap.yaml -n cnv-monitor
kubectl apply -f k8s/secret.yaml -n cnv-monitor
kubectl apply -f k8s/pvc.yaml -n cnv-monitor
kubectl apply -f k8s/deployment.yaml -n cnv-monitor
kubectl apply -f k8s/service.yaml -n cnv-monitor
kubectl apply -f k8s/route.yaml -n cnv-monitor
kubectl apply -f k8s/cronjob.yaml -n cnv-monitor
```

### Verify Deployment
```bash
kubectl get pods -n cnv-monitor
kubectl logs -f deployment/cnv-console-monitor -n cnv-monitor
kubectl get cronjob -n cnv-monitor
```

### Trigger Manual Poll
```bash
kubectl create job --from=cronjob/cnv-console-monitor-poll manual-poll -n cnv-monitor
kubectl logs job/manual-poll -n cnv-monitor --follow
```

